BASIC QUERIES 

SELECT IS ONE OF THE MOST important keyword IN SQL TO retrieve the data from DB

Select * from student   --- will retrieve all the data 
Select name from student  --- will retrieve only names 
Select student.name, student.major from student --- will retrieve only name and major 
Select student.name, student.major from student order by --- will retrieve only name and major and it 
will print on the basis of alphabetical order because order by keyword by default 
Select student.name, student.major from student order by DESC will retrieve only name and major and it 
will print on the basis of descending ORDER 

WE CAN also specify the column name to get in ascending(ASC) or descending(DESC) order 

LIMIT

Specific count of limit also possible to get for example

Select * from students
Limit 2
 
This statement will retrieve only two raws from DB

We can also set them as DESC ORDER for example 

Select * from students
Order by student_id DESC 
Limit 2

This statement will retrieve only two raws from DB on the basis of descending order of student id

WHERE is simply for filtering data 

For example 

Select * from students where student_id = 2;

IN

Select * from students where major IN ('biology', 'chemistry') AND student_id>=2;
IN keyword basically gives us what is inside of the pharentesis 
 
