UNIONS 

IS BASICALLY SPECIAL SQL OPERATOR WHICH WE CAN COMBINE MULTIPLE SELECT STATEMENTS INTO ONE 
WHEN using union operator need to follow some rules for example if in one select statement 2 column 
It has to be 2 column in another select statements as well and also data type has to be same to 
If one string another has to be string too 
Or one is integer another one also has to be integer 

For example 
SELECT first_name, last_name from employees
UNION
SELECT branch_name, branch_location from branch;


Another examples
-- find a list of all clients and branch suppliers names 

SELECT client_name, client.branch_id 
FROM client 
UNION
SELECT supplier_name, branch_supplier.branch id
FROM branch_supplier

-- find a list of all money spent or earned by the company 


