---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

WHERE vs HAVING 
Both clause is used to filter data

Where will filter at raw level individual raw 
Having will filter the data at group level where we use aggregate function 
Having cannot be used without group by clause in most cases 
For example 

Both where and having in one statement 

SELECT count(id), country 
FROM customer
WHERE country <> 'USA'
GROUP BY country 
HAVING COUNT (id) >= 9;

HAVING 
SELECT COUNT(salary), dept_id
FROM employees
GROUP BY dept_id
HAVING COUNT(salary) >5000;

WHERE 
SELECT * 
FROM employees
Where salary >5000; 












